01/03/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- In an official statement Sunday (29 February), Greek Defence Minister Yiannos Papantoniou dismissed a report in the <i>Financial Times</i> citing him as having suggested that Italian and Turkish navies should patrol the Aegean and Ionian seas. Greece would not allow foreign patrols on its territory, including sea and airspace, Papantoniou said. (ANA - 29/02/04)
